<h2 id="who-its-for">🎯 Who Shopify Plus Is For</h2>

**Ideal for:**
- Luxury DTC brands doing $1M-50M annually who prioritize reliability over maximum customization
- Brands with significant flash sale or limited-edition drop volume needing bulletproof infrastructure
- Companies wanting unified DTC and B2B on a single platform
- Teams with in-house developers or agency relationships comfortable with Liquid/Hydrogen
- International luxury brands needing multi-currency, multi-language without separate instances

**Not ideal for:**
- Brands requiring heavy content/editorial integration (consider headless CMS pairing)
- Companies with extremely complex product configurations (manufacturing, custom jewelry at scale)
- Businesses unwilling to invest in apps and development beyond base platform
- Brands doing under $500K annually (standard Shopify Advanced is likely sufficient)
- Companies requiring deep ERP integration with legacy systems (possible but expensive)

Our recommendation: if you're currently on standard Shopify and hitting limitations around checkout customization, automation complexity, or support response times, Plus is the logical upgrade. If you're evaluating Plus versus BigCommerce Enterprise or Adobe Commerce, the decision depends heavily on existing technical capabilities and specific customization requirements. Plus is fastest to launch but may not be cheapest long-term for highly customized implementations.

For deeper analysis of retail tech decisions, see our guide on [point of sale systems for multi-location retail](/reviews/pos-systems-multi-location-retail) which covers how POS selection impacts your ecommerce platform choice.

